title: Grateful Dead Live at Assembly Hall on 1981-12-02
lineage: Dat (Sony R500) -> Sound Devices 744T -> Samplitude Professional v11.03 -> FLAC
description:
Set 1

Bertha > Greatest Story Ever Told, Peggy-O, Mama Tried > Mexicali Blues, Brown Eyed Women, Passenger, Good Time Blues, Cumberland Blues, Looks Like Rain, China Cat Sunflower > I Know You Rider

Set 2

Feel Like A Stranger > Franklin's Tower, Lost Sailor > Saint Of Circumstance > Terrapin Station > Drums > Not Fade Away > Stella Blue > Around And Around > Good Lovin'

E: Don't Ease Me In

University Of Illinois

reviews.review_text: Lost Sailor > Saint Of Circumstance > Terrapin Station lost sailor is laid back slick... falls into a jammed saint that's waiting to show you turtle station
What a long 29 years My first show, and it caused many to follow 'til the end. Thanks for the pitch correction!

x factor drove from so cal  midwest tour  was in small venues met and talk to jerry in  hotel lobby  yes he took the time it was my friend  sal  who ended up buying tickets  from  garica  waiter from hotel  he and wife  dident wana  go the seats  where 5 rows  back 5 row up  on the left  side stage  passenger knock my socks off they tryed make me sitdown   but i justs  dances  away   its was worth  the ride

Winter '81: N3 Speedy Tower!  Crazy to think just over a year removed from those fall '80 acoustic residencies. Groovy NFA out of space. I hopped over to the new Miller SBD for the first then came back here for the second. Passenger liftoff!  Skip the NTAW and the whole second quarter is excellent. Charged China-Rider to close out the set. Really like the Peggy-O, too.

Never Trust a Woman Hate? Hey, at least it's not "Blow Away" or the lullaby they used to play instead of a killer "Wheel" outta "Space." "Never Trust a Woman" and "Hey Pockey Way" (a cover) are among the better tunes Brent played with the Dead.
